article.headline: Rider 74, Fairleigh Dickinson 72
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Terrance Mouton scored 23 points -- including two key 3-pointers in the closing minutes -- as Rider rallied for a 74-72 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Friday night. FDU (5-5) led 56-35 with just over 13 minutes left to play, but the Broncs (7-4) regained their shooting touch and finished the game with a 12-3 run, including Mouton's two 3-pointers. Mouton missed another 3-point attempt with 1:07 left, but the Broncs retained possession when Harris Mansell grabbed the rebound. Mouton eventually fed the ball to Mansell, who hit a 3-pointer with 40 seconds left to giver Rider a 73-72 lead. Jason Thompson then hit a free throw with five seconds to play, and Manny Ubilla's 3-point attempt at the buzzer was no good. Thompson finished with a game-high 24 points and 10 rebounds, while Mansell added 13 points and nine boards. Andre Harris led the Knights with 22 points and a game-high 14 rebounds, while Michael Peeples had 13 points and 11 boards.
